Congratulations on creating your first D: Congratulations on creating your first Data Product! This tour will introduce you to the key features that will help you manage and improve your Data Product effectively.
The About page of your Data Product func: The About page of your Data Product functions as a wiki page. Any relevant information about the Data Product can be documented here for easy reference by team members and stakeholders.
This tab lists the Input Ports for your: This tab lists the Input Ports for your Data Product. You can request access to additional Input Ports here.
Define the Output Ports for your Data Pr: Define the Output Ports for your Data Product and populate them with Technical Assets by dragging and dropping. Output Ports will automatically show up in the marketplace.
Assign roles and permissions to team mem: Assign roles and permissions to team members to manage access and collaboration effectively.
You are all set to start managing your D: You are all set to start managing your Data Product!
We have shown you the main features, but: We have shown you the main features, but feel free to explore further on your own.
With what you have learned you can:: With what you have learned you can:
Register Input Ports to bring data into: Register Input Ports to bring data into your Data Product.
Define Output Ports to expose data from: Define Output Ports to expose data from your Data Product.
Set up your team to manage access and co: Set up your team to manage access and collaboration.
If there are some concepts you are unsur: If there are some concepts you are unsure about, please refer to our <2>documentation</2> or reach out to support.
